You won't find a list of the words or sentences taught in the audio lessons, but instead we'll take you to the source, sounds of individual letters and letter combinations, and you'll learn how these sounds play out in words and sentences. Don't be afraid to push yourself with your pronunciation and accent. Be dramatic and have fun. The closer you can get to the native speaker's pronunciation, the more authentic your experience will be, and the better you'll remember. Eventually, when you've mastered the sound system, you'll be able to sound out words on sight and then read for meaning. By the end of the first 30 lessons, you will be reading at the same level as you are speaking.
